Appendix G: Glossary of Terms
Open
No
Attack Surface: The sum of all points where an unauthorized user can try to enter or
extract data
CVE: Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures - standardized identifier for security
vulnerabilities
CVSS: Common Vulnerability Scoring System - industry standard for assessing severity
CWE: Common Weakness Enumeration - categorization of software weaknesses
Exploit: Code or technique used to take advantage of a vulnerability
Penetration Testing: Authorized simulated attack to evaluate security
PoC: Proof of Concept - demonstration that vulnerability exists
Remediation: Process of fixing identified vulnerabilities
VAPT: Vulnerability Assessment and Penetration Testing
Zero-Day: Vulnerability unknown to vendor or without available patch
