Usage Notes for This Template
This template is designed for:
1. Professional penetration testing engagements
2. Portfolio demonstration
3. Educational purposes
4. Security assessment documentation
How to use:
1. Replace all [bracketed] placeholders with actual data
2. Remove sections not applicable to your assessment
3. Add custom sections as needed for your specific engagement
4. Ensure all findings follow the detailed template format
5. Include actual evidence (screenshots, logs, etc.)
6. Customize methodology to match your approach
Best Practices:
Use clear, non-technical language in Executive Summary
Include visual aids (diagrams, charts, screenshots)
Provide specific, actionable remediation steps
Include both technical and business impact
Reference industry standards and frameworks
Maintain professional tone throughout
Proofread thoroughly before delivery
Remember:
Never include client confidential information in public portfolios
Anonymize all real assessment data
Use generic examples for portfolio demonstration
Always obtain client permission before sharing any details
